Telkom will adjust the price of its fixed-line products on 1 September 2019, including price increases on its line rental and ADSL products. The company also announced that its fixed customers on wireless technology will be migrated to SmartVoice during August 2019 and will not be impacted by the rate adjustment. There three main Telkom fixed-line services will see price changes: The price for line rental, which all ADSL subscribers must pay, will increase from the current R200.74 to R210.00. The company announced that customers on DSL bundles which were expired (no longer available for sale) will also be subject to the tariff increases. The tables below provide an overview of the Telkom price increases which will kick in on 1 September 2019.